Khartoum &mdash; The Undersecretary of the Ministry of Animal Resources Dr. Kamal Tajal-Sir has been appointed as a member of the Executive Council of the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE), which consists of 180 countries from around the world at its annual meeting in Paris, France.Dr. Tajal-Sir was selected by to represent Africa 54 African countries in the elections held in early May in Nairobi.The OIE Executive Council consists of a president and six members representing the continents of the world.